[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] +## 10. AI Coding Agent Integration
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr]  
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] -```bash
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] -# Prerequisites: Node.js >= 18, pnpm >= 8
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] +This codebase is designed to be **AI coding agent-friendly**. The following design decisions make the code predictable, statically analyzable, and safe to modify through automated tooling.
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] -## 10. Getting Started
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr]  
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] +### Why AI Agents Work Well Here
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| Property | Benefit for AI Agents |
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| **Clean Architecture** | Strict layer separation makes it easy to identify where code belongs |
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| **Strict TypeScript** | Full type information enables safe refactoring and accurate code generation |
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] +|----------|-----------------------|
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| **Repository Pattern** | Data access follows a predictable, consistent interface |
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| **Pure Domain Logic** | Domain packages have zero framework dependencies, making them easy to test and modify |
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| **Feature Modules** | New features can mirror existing patterns exactly |
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] +### How AI Agents Should Approach This Codebase
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| **Zod Validation** | Every data boundary is explicitly defined and validated |
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| **Pre-built CodeGraph Index** | Symbol search, caller/callee analysis, and blast radius computation available out of the box |
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] +2. **Use CodeGraph** — Run `codegraph explore "<question>"` for structural answers instead of grepping files
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] +3. **Follow the data flow** — `Component → Hook → Service → Repository → IndexedDB`. Never call the database directly from UI
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] +1. **Start with the architecture** — Read this document and [architecture.md](architecture.md) for layer separation understanding
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] +5. **Validate with Zod** — Every data boundary requires a Zod schema
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] +4. **Mirror existing patterns** — New features should follow the same structure as existing feature modules
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] +6. **Respect layer isolation** — Domain packages must not import from Presentation or Infrastructure layers
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] +### Available Agent Tools
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- **Symbol Search** — Find any symbol by name
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] +The `.codegraph/` index provides pre-computed structural knowledge:
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- **Caller/Cal** — List every call site of a function, including callback registrations
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- **Blast Radius** — Determine what a change would affect
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.351Z] [INFO] [stderr] +For detailed AI agent guidelines, see [ai-agent.md](ai-agent.md).
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.350Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.351Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-07T04:39:29.351Z] [INFO] [stderr] +---
